Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.95,0:01:58.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Ass-to-what observation?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.75,0:02:00.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Genta-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.78,0:02:04.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Astronomical observation, astronomical observation!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.45,0:02:08.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Doc, are we gonna see the stars?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.39,0:02:12.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I found a little hostel in the Gunma mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.25,0:02:17.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why are we going out and looking at stars when it's so cold out?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.65,0:02:19.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's better to go on a cold night.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.15,0:02:23.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The air is clearer on cold days. It's easier to see the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.65,0:02:25.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, tonight is the new moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.95,0:02:28.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a perfect night for stargazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.15,0:02:34.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't it boring, just looking at stars?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.49,0:02:36.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.35,0:02:38.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll teach you the constellations,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.45,0:02:44.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and if you find a new celestial object, you might just be able to name it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.25,0:02:46.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Name?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.05,0:02:48.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A star...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.73,0:02:50.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We can name it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.85,0:02:52.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.95,0:02:56.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we won't be able to name an asteroid,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.90,0:03:00.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,because it has to be observed multiple times and its orbit must be confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.35,0:03:03.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But maybe we can find a comet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.35,0:03:07.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So how about calling it the "Beika Detective Boys Comet"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.05,0:03:09.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.23,0:03:10.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, right? That would be great.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.62,0:03:11.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.05,0:03:15.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't give it just any name. That's only for asteroids.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.75,0:03:18.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Comets are given the last names of the people who found them,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.25,0:03:21.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and only the names of the first three people who spotted the comet are used.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.35,0:03:26.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. If the comet was spotted in different parts of the world at the same time,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.45,0:03:29.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it could end up having names of people from different countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.85,0:03:33.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Three people... Me and... uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.85,0:03:37.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Like the "Kobayashi-Berger-Milon" comet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.85,0:03:41.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So if we find the comet and report it right away,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.65,0:03:46.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it could be the "Yoshida-\NTsuburaya-Haibara Comet", right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.25,0:03:47.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right? Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.79,0:03:48.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.90,0:03:52.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Yoshida... Tsuburaya... Haibara...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.33,0:03:56.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How come my name isn't in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.25,0:03:58.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I want Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s name on it too!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.94,0:04:01.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But you can only use three people...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.36,0:04:04.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0} too...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.33,0:04:06.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.29,0:04:12.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, that's Masaharu Motoyama-{\i1}san{\i0}, the sports reporter
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.15,0:04:15.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,who murdered pro baseball player Nose in Okinawa the other day!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.15,0:04:17.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were there when it happened, right, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.95,0:04:21.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I was wondering a bit about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.25,0:04:23.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wondering?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.95,0:04:26.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, uh, it's no big deal!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.65,0:04:31.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I just wondered who the other person was he was calling on his cell during a police questioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.75,0:04:38.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The police had already told Nose's family about his death...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.25,0:04:42.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I'd think it was someone Motoyama-{\i1}san{\i0} himself knew, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.45,0:04:43.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.90,0:04:46.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I should've just asked him directly at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.15,0:04:50.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it was Komori?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.95,0:04:54.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Considering he was teammates with Nose and Motoyama...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.25,0:04:59.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They did TV specials together during the off-season,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.15,0:05:00.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and they seemed like good friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.35,0:05:04.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he called him about their mutual friend's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.05,0:05:09.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He retired four years ago and took over his family business, running an inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.85,0:05:13.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's a place in Tottori called Kurayoshi...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.05,0:05:16.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They used to advertise it on the TV specials.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.65,0:05:19.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It seemed like a nice place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.15,0:05:20.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.85,0:05:25.24,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I guess it didn't have anything to do with the men in black...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.15,0:05:30.05,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Kurayoshi...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.05,0:05:33.35,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Kudo-{\i1}kun{\i0}, don't tell me you...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.71,0:05:49.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Agasa-{\i1}sama{\i0}, right? I've been waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.22,0:05:50.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please sign your name in the guestbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.85,0:05:52.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.15,0:05:55.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiroshi Agasa...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.05,0:05:56.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.85,0:06:00.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Asao invited you here too, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.15,0:06:05.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, tell me...\NI want to apologize to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.03,0:06:07.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is Asao?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.15,0:06:09.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's Asao?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.45,0:06:10.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't play dumb with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.05,0:06:14.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The guy wearing the same ring as me! Asao Kono!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.42,0:06:17.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He sent you an invitation too, didn't he?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.69,0:06:18.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Nonomiya-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.60,0:06:20.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Invitation?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.25,0:06:24.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, no... This is the first time we've ever been here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.05,0:06:27.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.26,0:06:29.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.21,0:06:33.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What a shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.05,0:06:34.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.43,0:06:36.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.05,0:06:40.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was Etsuko Nonomiya. She was my {\i1}kohai{\i0} at university.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.95,0:06:45.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That Kono-{\i1}kun{\i0} she was talking about was my {\i1}kohai{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.08,0:06:47.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They got engaged a while back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.34,0:06:50.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They used to stay here often,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.12,0:06:53.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but last year they got into a huge fight here,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.29,0:06:56.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and after that he just disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.35,0:07:02.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She suddenly received an invitation from him last week telling her to meet him here,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.69,0:07:04.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and she's been waiting for three days now,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.41,0:07:07.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but he still hasn't shown up,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.85,0:07:09.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and in the meantime, she's been drinking nonstop.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.29,0:07:13.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't even know him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.75,0:07:16.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What made her think I'd received an invitation?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.35,0:07:17.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.35,0:07:21.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know him either, but check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.60,0:07:25.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We both got invitations from this Kono guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.45,0:07:30.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we did meet him once, on that day a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.65,0:07:34.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the invitation was so intriguing we decided to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.59,0:07:37.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, can I take a look at the invitation?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.23,0:07:39.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.16,0:07:41.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.65,0:07:47.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"After a year's observation, I have made an unbelievable discovery..."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.65,0:07:49.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"that will shake the astronomical world."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.15,0:07:51.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"I would like to ask your advice,"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.31,0:07:54.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"so please meet me at the Amatsuchi Inn."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.05,0:07:57.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Naturally, I will pay for your stay."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.83,0:08:00.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"If you are busy and unable to come, there's nothing I can do about it."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.95,0:08:02.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Signed Asao Kono."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.99,0:08:07.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We've been waiting for two days now and he hasn't appeared,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.70,0:08:09.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so it looks like it was just a prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.05,0:08:12.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready to leave, Editor-in-Chief?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.45,0:08:14.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,E-Editor-in-Chief?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.75,0:08:18.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. We publish an astronomy magazine called {\i1}Space Sunday{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.10,0:08:22.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and Mikami-{\i1}san{\i0} is its editor-in-chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.25,0:08:26.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He ain't no ordinary editor-in-chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.37,0:08:27.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.65,0:08:28.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.15,0:08:33.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey... What do you mean,\N"he isn't an ordinary editor-in-chief"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.65,0:08:39.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a great guy! He's even had a comet named after him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.66,0:08:42.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He found one?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.05,0:08:43.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you find it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.39,0:08:45.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You have to tell us!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.05,0:08:47.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Er, it's hard to say where...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.45,0:08:49.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Over here? Or over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.75,0:08:50.65,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hey, hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.12,0:08:54.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Try climbing the hill out behind the inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.95,0:08:58.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can get a good clear view.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.00,0:09:00.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the perfect spot for stargazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.45,0:09:04.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll even rent you a telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.65,0:09:05.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's 5,000 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.01,0:09:08.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a charge, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.65,0:09:11.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.35,0:09:12.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.65,0:09:16.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! We're gonna find our own star!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.02,0:09:17.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.58,0:09:19.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Rank amateurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.05,0:09:22.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No way they'll find anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.15,0:09:24.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ain't that right, Editor-in-Chief?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.55,0:09:25.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.29,0:09:27.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you never know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.17,0:09:32.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how much you know, in the end finding a star comes down to luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.25,0:09:35.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're lucky, you can find your star...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.55,0:09:37.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mr. Editor...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.85,0:09:43.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were lucky to find a star, so can you look for mine as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.35,0:09:47.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He disappeared into the darkness of space, chasing stars of his own...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.10,0:09:51.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My dear, dear man...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.73,0:09:57.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's further than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.80,0:09:59.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can do it, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.10,0:10:01.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.69,0:10:08.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that's gotta be the hill he told us about!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.60,0:10:11.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's more of a cliff than a hill.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.96,0:10:14.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you telling me we've got to climb this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.12,0:10:16.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,L-Let me take a break...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.25,0:10:19.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, if we're gonna do it, we'd better do it before it gets dark!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.13,0:10:22.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Be kind to your elders!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.69,0:10:26.45,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}You're always telling me not to treat you like an old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.96,0:10:28.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How about a ten-minute break?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.95,0:10:30.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Good idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.53,0:10:32.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh. There's no helping them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.00,0:10:41.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A rock... A rock...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.80,0:10:44.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But don't you think there's something weird about that invitation?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.00,0:10:48.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"If you are busy and unable to come, there's nothing I can do about it"...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.84,0:10:50.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why write something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.55,0:10:51.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.15,0:10:53.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There must be a reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.05,0:10:56.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why invite those particular people?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.78,0:10:59.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Found one!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.45,0:11:10.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Ayumi-{\i1}chan{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.85,0:11:13.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-A skull!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.05,0:11:15.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For real?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.72,0:11:18.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What's a skull doing here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.00,0:11:19.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There are more bones scattered here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.45,0:11:21.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.75,0:11:22.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A lower jawbone...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.81,0:11:23.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,An upper arm bone...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.41,0:11:25.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A leg bone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.05,0:11:27.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the rest of the body...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.75,0:11:28.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.55,0:11:31.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I can't believe my eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.30,0:11:36.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This person must've fallen off the cliff!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.46,0:11:38.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.95,0:11:43.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably the skeleton of someone who died in an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.45,0:11:46.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The bones were scattered by animals and the wind and rain...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.52,0:11:47.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.75,0:11:51.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a murder. And a gruesome one at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.75,0:11:54.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look. Quicklime.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.85,0:11:58.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When quicklime absorbs water, it gives off heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.95,0:12:02.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you sprinkle it around a body, it'll produce heat when it rains.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.10,0:12:07.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That speeds up decomposition. Someone wanted to create a skeleton quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.15,0:12:11.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That makes it just about impossible to determine the cause or time of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.65,0:12:14.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Maybe that skull...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.35,0:12:17.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,is that Kono-{\i1}san{\i0} person those other people were talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.15,0:12:18.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.15,0:12:21.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He only just sent them those invitations...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.85,0:12:23.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It probably is that Kono-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.35,0:12:28.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look under this rock. A ring and a carton of cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.90,0:12:32.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Engraved on this ring, it says in English, "Etsuko to Asao".
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.92,0:12:39.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He must've hidden them before the killer came down here after pushing him off the cliff,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.75,0:12:43.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,in the hope that someone would find them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.85,0:12:46.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Or the killer planted them here on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.23,0:12:49.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, the killer would've left the ring on his finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.85,0:12:53.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, the killer went to all this trouble
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.31,0:12:55.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to make the body unidentifiable.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.34,0:12:57.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can somebody lend me a handkerchief?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.65,0:13:00.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.55,0:13:01.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.45,0:13:04.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So what's the cigarette carton for?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.55,0:13:07.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If my deductions are correct, this is probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.95,0:13:15.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing in it but cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.45,0:13:16.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.95,0:13:19.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Could this be...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.08,0:13:22.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Kono-{\i1}san{\i0} left them behind...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.55,0:13:24.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,as a dying message.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.17,0:13:27.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Dying message?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.40,0:13:34.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,These cigarettes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.15,0:13:35.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.15,0:13:41.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely, Asao Kono left them as a clue pointing to his murderer before he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.10,0:13:46.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't it just six cigarettes, with two of them broken in half?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.25,0:13:48.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a closer look!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.68,0:13:52.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The two short cigarettes both have filters, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.40,0:13:57.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This shows that he broke them on purpose and threw away the other halves.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.78,0:13:58.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And here,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.85,0:14:02.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,if you look carefully under the rock where the cigarette carton was hidden,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.00,0:14:07.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you see the decaying remnants of the other cigarettes, including the broken halves, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.12,0:14:10.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, Kono left this...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.05,0:14:13.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to tell us that the clue is in the four long cigarettes...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.62,0:14:16.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the two short cigarettes in the carton.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.80,0:14:21.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Anyway, I'd better call the hostel about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.10,0:14:21.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it, Doc!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.97,0:14:24.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If they find out at the hostel, it will be bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.95,0:14:25.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Call the police first!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.95,0:14:27.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.65,0:14:28.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.75,0:14:34.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All the guests at the hostel right now are people who received invitations from Kono-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.15,0:14:37.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If those bones really belong to Kono-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.64,0:14:40.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then the invitations were sent by someone else, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.85,0:14:45.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the people who were invited were all staying at the hostel
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.12,0:14:48.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when Kono-{\i1}san{\i0} disappeared a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.77,0:14:54.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If these scattered bones are not the result of wind, rain or animals,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.65,0:14:57.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but were placed like this on purpose...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.67,0:14:58.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.23,0:15:03.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoever sent those invitations may have wanted somebody to find Kono-{\i1}san{\i0}'s skeleton,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.11,0:15:07.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,as part of a fiendish scheme.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.85,0:15:10.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of scheme?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.45,0:15:11.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.85,0:15:14.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, call the police! Tell them to come right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.78,0:15:16.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Doc?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.05,0:15:18.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.77,0:15:22.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like I can't get a signal out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.25,0:15:24.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Meh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.91,0:15:27.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go back to the hostel and call the cops...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.61,0:15:30.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,P-Police?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.20,0:15:32.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Has something happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.10,0:15:35.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Amatsuchi-{\i1}san{\i0}! What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.22,0:15:40.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot to include the weight for the telescope in the bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.25,0:15:43.15,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.62,0:15:44.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.45,0:15:45.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.65,0:15:46.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.29,0:15:48.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, er, weight? What for?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.70,0:15:49.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.25,0:15:52.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-Bones?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.15,0:15:55.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.55,0:15:56.05,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Drat!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.33,0:16:00.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? You found Asao's bones in the forest?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.20,0:16:03.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But they're just bones, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.14,0:16:05.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't tell if it's Asao or not!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.50,0:16:08.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, near the bones we also found...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.65,0:16:13.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,an engagement ring with your and his initials carved on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.25,0:16:20.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, maybe this Asao Kono guy's the killer, and planted the ring on his victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.28,0:16:23.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But we found the ring under...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.75,0:16:26.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, by any chance did that Kono-{\i1}san{\i0} have a cavity?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.25,0:16:31.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In the second tooth from the back, on the right side of his upper jaw?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.05,0:16:33.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A back tooth in his upper jaw?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.79,0:16:40.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then those bones aren't Asao.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.15,0:16:46.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He did have a cavity, but it was in a front tooth on the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.55,0:16:48.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.55,0:16:48.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So it really is...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.51,0:16:49.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.06,0:16:51.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait, what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.55,0:16:52.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.15,0:16:58.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to say, but we found a filling in the central incisor on the mandible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.75,0:17:02.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, a front tooth on the bottom, just as you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.25,0:17:08.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To see if you would lie or simply agree with his story,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.56,0:17:10.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he intentionally said the cavity was in the wrong tooth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.16,0:17:11.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.05,0:17:13.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.45,0:17:18.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then Asao...Asao is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.88,0:17:25.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, you have to call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.93,0:17:28.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I can't. The phone isn't working.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.78,0:17:33.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that phone's electrical cord is plugged in,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.65,0:17:35.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but the phone cable's missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.17,0:17:38.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.35,0:17:43.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Strange. It was working fine until just a moment ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.55,0:17:45.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any other phones or spare cables?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.05,0:17:47.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the only phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.95,0:17:49.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And I don't have any spare cables.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.55,0:17:53.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So we can't call the police...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.12,0:17:54.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You've gotta be kidding me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.54,0:17:56.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm getting in my car and leaving!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.00,0:17:58.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, Editor!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.60,0:17:59.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.45,0:18:02.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but you can't do that either.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.49,0:18:05.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I just checked outside,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.35,0:18:09.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and all the cars have flat tires.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.75,0:18:13.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like somebody loosened the valves and let the air out,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.55,0:18:16.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so we wouldn't be able to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.15,0:18:18.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We're all trapped here together.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.55,0:18:21.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I can't believe this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.75,0:18:26.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't tell me this has something to do with that Kono guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.57,0:18:27.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You bet it does!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.70,0:18:28.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It does, it does!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.64,0:18:30.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, he was mur—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.25,0:18:34.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, you kids were looking at something when I found the bones, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.75,0:18:40.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Four long cigarettes and two short cigarettes that you'd placed in a handkerchief.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.15,0:18:44.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, maybe it's a dying message?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.50,0:18:47.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.95,0:18:49.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.80,0:18:52.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no dying message.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.59,0:18:56.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Asao's just playing dead to make me suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.95,0:18:58.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's so naughty.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.75,0:19:00.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Asao would never die.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.45,0:19:03.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What a cute guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.17,0:19:05.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I think we should take not one step out of our rooms tonight,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.22,0:19:09.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and just wait for morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.55,0:19:35.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There are six cigarettes—four long and two short.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.25,0:19:38.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's too many to spell Futagawa-{\i1}san{\i0} in kanji,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.35,0:19:40.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and one too few to spell Amatsuchi-{\i1}san{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.23,0:19:44.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And spelling Nonomiya-{\i1}san{\i0} or Mikami-{\i1}san{\i0} is out of the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.05,0:19:46.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's katakana?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.25,0:19:48.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.80,0:19:50.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It would take 14 to write Futagawa-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.93,0:19:52.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,12 to write Amatsuchi-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.95,0:19:54.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,8 for Nonomiya-{\i1}san{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.97,0:19:58.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and 9 if we wanted to write Mikami-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.50,0:20:00.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What about initials, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.70,0:20:04.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See, "Haibara, Ai" would be HA, exactly 6 lines...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.47,0:20:10.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Then {\i1}you're{\i0} the murderer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.87,0:20:13.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Merely offering an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.86,0:20:15.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.81,0:20:19.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, "TM" for "Tsuburaya, Mitsuhiko"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.73,0:20:22.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and "YA" for "Yoshida, Ayumi" also use 6.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.90,0:20:23.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.27,0:20:26.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm, "Kojima, Genta" is...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.42,0:20:31.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All three of us take 6! It's so romantic!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.25,0:20:35.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I take 6 too—"AH" for "Agasa, Hiroshi".
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.05,0:20:38.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh, it's just a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.75,0:20:39.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.15,0:20:43.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps these initials could be the right answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.55,0:20:48.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? The killer is Futagawa-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.05,0:20:52.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if the cigarettes are meant to spell out initials, he's the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.23,0:20:55.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Amatsuchi, Ryoji"-{\i1}san{\i0} is AR.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.55,0:20:57.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,, "Nonomiya, Etsuko"-{\i1}san{\i0} is NE.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.00,0:20:59.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Mikami, Heihachi"-{\i1}san{\i0} is MH.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.58,0:21:04.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only name you can get out of 6 cigarettes is "FH" for "Futagawa, Hajime", right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.55,0:21:08.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But is it safe to confront that Futagawa-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.15,0:21:10.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. We'll just trick him into confessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.81,0:21:15.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.52,0:21:17.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like Futagawa-{\i1}san{\i0} isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.25,0:21:22.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This cigarette filter's still damp.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.95,0:21:25.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It hasn't been long since he left his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.65,0:21:28.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone's walking around outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.39,0:21:30.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Nonomiya-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.26,0:21:32.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.44,0:21:33.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just Futagawa-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.85,0:21:36.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikami-{\i1}san{\i0} and Amatsuchi-{\i1}san{\i0} are gone too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.87,0:21:37.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.55,0:21:39.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We told them not to go outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.45,0:21:42.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, Mitsuhiko, Ayumi-{\i1}chan{\i0} and I will bring Nonomiya-{\i1}san{\i0} back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.96,0:21:45.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Doc, Haibara and Genta, go look for the other three!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.95,0:21:47.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Alright, will do!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.06,0:21:49.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nonomiya-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.36,0:21:50.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.99,0:21:52.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Oneesan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.06,0:21:58.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, isn't this the path that leads to the skeleton?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.11,0:21:59.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? You don't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.90,0:22:02.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She wanted to find out for herself if those bones were really Kono-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.96,0:22:04.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.05,0:22:07.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that sound just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.00,0:22:09.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Futagawa-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.95,0:22:12.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We're too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.11,0:22:14.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His neck is broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.51,0:22:16.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's already stopped breathing...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.40,0:22:19.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-He's holding on to something.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.17,0:22:21.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A cigarette carton?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.40,0:22:26.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it the same dying message again?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.13,0:22:27.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.01,0:22:31.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This time, there's one more cigarette.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.33,0:24:02.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey! Don't turn the place upside-down!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.14,0:24:07.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you brought your own telescope?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.65,0:24:09.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How long are you going to search my room?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.60,0:24:12.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only thing that could be used as a weapon is this umbrella.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.16,0:24:17.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All that's left, Amatsuchi-{\i1}san{\i0}, is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.99,0:24:20.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He kept looking at the guestbook!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.80,0:24:22.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Over and over again!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.75,0:24:24.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.08,0:24:30.09,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.51,0:24:35.05,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Next Conan's Hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.51,0:24:35.05,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Initials
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.32,0:24:36.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Next week it's case closed!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.38,0:24:38.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Promise you'll watch my great performance.
